As an AI language model, I don't have access to user interface and code, therefore I can't write code nor run apps. However, here is an example of how you can listen for screen size changes in your Flutter app using MediaQuery and LayoutBuilder:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: Scaffold(
        body: LayoutBuilder(
          builder: (BuildContext context, BoxConstraints constraints) {
            return Center(
              child: Text(
                'Current screen width: ${constraints.maxWidth}',
                style: TextStyle(fontSize: 20),
              ),
            );
          },
        ),
      ),
